.TH SPACEGL_CLIENT 1 "2026-04-19" "SpaceGL @VERSION@" "SpaceGL Manual"
.SH NAME
spacegl_client \- SpaceGL tactical bridge client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spacegl_client
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ gl | vk ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B spacegl_client
is the network client for the SpaceGL multi-user 3D space engine.
It connects to a running
.BR spacegl_server (1)
instance, synchronizes galaxy state via shared memory (SHM), and
launches the appropriate 3D frontend.
.PP
Pass
.B gl
to launch the OpenGL frontend
.RB ( spacegl_3dview )
or
.B vk
to launch the Vulkan frontend
.RB ( spacegl_vulkan ).
.PP
Authentication is performed through a master key provided via the
.B SPACEGL_KEY
environment variable or interactively at startup.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B gl
Start with the OpenGL (GLUT/GLEW) 3D view.
.TP
.B vk
Start with the Vulkan 3D view.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SPACEGL_KEY
Authentication key used to connect to the server.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/spacegl_client
Client executable.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR spacegl_server (1),
.BR spacegl_client.sh (1),
.BR spacegl_3dview (1),
.BR spacegl_vulkan (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Nicola Taibi
